Sentence1: In three patients, there was concomitant overexpression of  FGFR3  and  FGFR4 .
Sentence2: Intriguingly, among the eight PDAC cases that did not harbor a  KRAS  mutation, four cases had either amplification or increased expression of the  FGF19 ,  FGF4 ,  FGF3 , and  CCND1  genes, and six cases had  RAD9A  and  RPS6KB2  gene overexpression, two of which were due to amplification ( Figure 2 A), raising the possibility that a portion of the 11q13.3 amplicon helps drive PDAC development in the absence of mutated  KRAS .
